title: The Squid
author: Sprocketlord
pages:
#- 
       
        THE SQUID
             
            by

      Sprocketlord
#- 
Goodbye, world of wonder. 

I knew thee fairly well.

The tides took me wonderfully,

to my underwater hell.
#- 
I started off quite curious,

"What lives beneath the sea?"

I shouldn't have searched.

Damn my curiosity!
#- 
White serpents filled the water first,

and slither slickly this they did.

But slick serpents knew not bravery,

from the smallest birds they hid!
#- 
Foolish me, wandering free.

To find a beast beneath the sea.

But the curse of the wanderer is

how empty life can
be.
#- 

You fill your barren shelves with curios.

To line an empty hall.

But to live life uncurious,

is not to live at all.
#- 
A sage is curious,

but thinks before the hunt.

A fool may be sagacious,

but he will always get the blunt.
#- 

And thus I dove deep under,

to find the stories hid.

And only underwater,

my questions would I rid.
#- 
But questions are confusing

they stay unanswered for a reason.

And confusion is natural

In any of lifes seasons.

#- 
Don't go seeking answers,

for the mystery isn't there.

And danger always does the answering,

With Fates thread as a snare.
#- 
My corporeal form the beast did crush.

Knowledge has it's price.

But my incorporeal dreams

prove you can indeed live twice.
#- 
Flighty men lament my loss.

They count me brave
for that I did.

But the wise man knows not bravery,

he only knows the SQUID. 
#- 

ORIGINAL COPY

DO NOT REPRINT

-Sprocketlord
#- 